sub_title: Senior case assessor at the Dutch Revenue service
summary:
With a Master’s degree in comparative company law, I am currently working as an administrative lawyer at the Dutch Revenue service. Here, I deal with the consequences of the Dutch childcare benefits scandal and its effects on the parents involved. 

In my work I have gained experience in working in teams and dealing with a great variety of people, and during my studies I have twice spent a semester abroad. Accuracy, determination and commitment are distinctive of me, as is a studious and thorough attitude. 

I look forward to a new challenge abroad, to continuously gain new knowledge and expertise, and to use and develop my legal and linguistic skills further.
